[<p>The head of the attorney general\u2019s charities bureau James Sheehan said if the Trump Foundation\xa0doesn\u2019t\xa0file the proper paperwork and stop fundraising, it would be committing \u201ca continuing fraud upon the people of New York.\u201d</p>, <p>Trump\u2019s foundation was ordered to hand over the required legal paperwork for charities within 15 days, according to the <a href="/web/20161005062131/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trump-foundation-ordered-to-stop-fundraising-by-ny-attorney-generals-office/2016/10/03/1d4d295a-8987-11e6-bff0-d53f592f176e_story.html"><em>Washington Post</em></a>.</p>, <p>Trump\u2019s spokesperson Hope Hicks reacted to the order on Monday, saying,\xa0\u201cWhile we remain very concerned about the political motives behind A.G. Schneiderman\u2019s investigation, the Trump Foundation nevertheless intends to cooperate fully with the investigation.\u201d</p>, <p>Hicks\xa0<a href="/web/20161005062131/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/04/us/politics/trump-foundation-money.html?_r=0">added</a>,\u201cBecause this is an ongoing legal matter, the Trump Foundation will not comment further at this time.\u201d</p>]